Serious concerns have been raised on the credibility of the just concluded Kenya Certificate of Primary Education, KCPE, exams. The controversy is arising from a claim that most of the questions in the english language paper were lifted from a test and two books that had been in huge circulation and distribution during the month of February. however, the ministry of education has moved to allay fears of cheating and exam leaks compromising the 2020 KCPE exams. Let's get more from KTN's Shadrack Mitty.